SUMMARY:Bloom & Begin: An Ostara Intention Workshop
DESCRIPTION:The spring equinox is a time of perfect balance—where light overtakes the dark and the earth begins its big wake-up call. We’re gathering to shake off the winter slumber and get intentional about what we’re planting for the months ahead. \n*Reflective Meditation: We’ll start by getting quiet and centered. This guided session is designed to help you “thaw out” and identify the specific intentions or goals you want to carry through the rest of the year.\n*Botanical Intention Art: Once your intentions are clear\, you’ll bring them to life. You’ll choose from three Ostara-inspired flower templates\, using the lines of the petals and stem to scribe your personal affirmations or goals. It’s a beautiful\, visual piece of magic you can take home and keep on your altar or desk.\n*Curated Altar Shopping: Not sure what you need for your spring celebrations? We’ve got you. We’ll provide a “cheat sheet” of helpful altar supplies (crystals\, herbs\, and candles) that you can shop for right here in-store to round out your Ostara kit.
URL:https://downtowndurham.com/event/bloom-begin-an-ostara-intention-workshop/
LOCATION:Fate & Folklore\, 123 Market Street\, Durham\, NC\, United States
CATEGORIES:Accessible,Art,Community Engagement,Craft,Shopping,Spiritual/Religious
